    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi \colon  A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/jms-00LO/" title="Predicate" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LO/" display-uri="jms-00LO" type="local">predicate</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. The <html:em><html:strong>comprehension</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> is defined to be the following subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [\phi \right  ]\mathclose {}}\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> spanned by elements at which <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi ]]></fr:tex> holds, as specified below:</html:p>
